{
  "texts": [
    "As regards the attempts to make AIs more compatible with neuroscience we already mentioned the issue of Explainable AI (XAI), namely the \"explainability\" problem of AI technologies, and the proposed solution (Taylor and Taylor, 2021; Iglesias, 2022) to import assessment methods developed in Psychology and Cognitive Neuroscience: although this may be a useful method of analysis, it is of no help from the \"generative\" point of view, i.e., for the design of autonomous, prospective cognitive agents.",
    "Another stream of neuro-inspired AI is Embodied AIs (Duan et al., 2022): please, note the plural, with the implicit assumption that Intelligence or Cognition is not the fundamental organizational principle from which all the specific competences are derived and integrated but is rather the result of the mere assembly of specific and substantially independent AIs, like perceiving, skilled gesturing, abstraction discovering, planning, modeling other agents, self and social awareness, interacting, and communicating.",
    "Embodied AI research diverges from conventional AI where learning is orchestrated on collecting big data and using them separately for different functions (perception, motor control, planning, etc.)",
    "with a third-person (impersonal) view of the acquired knowledge.",
    "In contrast, embodied AI is characterized by a first-person perspective that aims at mimicking human behavior during the interaction with the environment."
  ]
}